description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for RN / RSCN to join our happy and cohesive ED team as we start a multi million transformation and expansion. Are you enthusiastic, motivated, keen learner, innovative and forward thinking? If so, we would like to hear from you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a busy working environment with a high turnover of patients which sees and treats children and adults with a range of conditions including minor injuries, major trauma, medical and surgical emergencies and mental health conditions. Clinical working areas include Majors, Minors, EDAU and Resus. We have a dedicated clinical practice educator to ensure robust support and education as you begin your new journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have full-time band 5 Staff Nurse vacancies within our busy Emergency Department at Dorset County Hospital NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Successful applicants should have good communication skills and enjoy working in a swiftly changing and challenging environment. You will be required to work as part of a motivated team as well as being able to work on own initiative. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Opportunities exist to develop personal practice and gain experience in all aspects of emergency care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clare Turnbull, ED Matron on 01305 254917 or &lt;span&gt;Senior Sisters Katy Jeffs and Sarah Sedgbeer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
